          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_797808208:2c61cf071130",
            "label": "Please provide a brief explanation of the why this request is necessary for FY27?",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Restores stability to the U.S. space science workforce following the disruption of FY 2026 funding cuts and the loss of thousands of specialized technical roles\n* Counteracts rapid expansion of Chinese space science ambitions to ensure the United States continues to set global norms for 21st-century exploration\n* Funds high-priority missions identified by the National Academies Decadal Surveys, representing the nonpartisan consensus of the scientific community\n* Maintains a critical 3-to-1 economic return on investment that supports the broader aerospace, technology, and innovation industrial base",
            "rationale": "Based on advocacy talking points regarding workforce stability, strategic competition with China, and economic ROI.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_997931178:0c0591489b86",
            "label": "Why is this request important to Illinois and the 3rd Congressional District? ",
            "help_text": "Explain the local impact and importance of this request.",
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": true,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Directly supports $133,404 in grant funding for North Park University in Chicago for AERONET sensor installation to boost minority STEM participation\n* Sustains economic activity in the 3rd District, which has received over $210,000 in NASA Science obligations between FY 2023 and FY 2025\n* Enables local businesses like Atp Gov, LLC and Wittenstein, Inc. to participate in the high-tech aerospace and defense supply chain\n* Strengthens the local talent pipeline by providing inspiration and research opportunities for the next generation of Illinois-based scientists and engineers",
            "rationale": "Cites specific local award data for North Park University and local contractors Atp Gov and Wittenstein, Inc. from the NASA spending context.",
            "confidence": "high"
          },
          {
            "field_id": "google_forms:01:entry_267650217:92d4dbd52a88",
            "label": "Other notes/comments",
            "help_text": null,
            "field_type": "textarea",
            "required": false,
            "options": null,
            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* Backed by major scientific organizations including the American Astronomical Society (AAS) and American Geophysical Union (AGU)\n* Follows strong bipartisan support in Congress to restore NASA Science funding after major cuts were proposed in previous budget cycles\n* Advances fundamental public responsibilities codified in Title 51 that generate national prestige and unique scientific breakthroughs\n* Aligns with high public approval for space science, which is consistently cited as a top non-partisan priority in national polling",
